;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>话题：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tWriting: imagine a scenario or express your opinion<br />\n\tStretch<br />\n\tTo stretch means to extend to a greater length. Who is stretching? What is being stretched? What is the reason?<br />\n\tThis week's topic: They were stretching... (90-110 words)</p>\n<p>\n\tSuggestions:<br />\n\t1) stretch before exercising<br />\n\t2) stretching the deadline<br />\n\t3) is cable is stretched<br />\n\t4) stretching oneself too thin<br />\n\t5) Instead of writing a scenario, feel free to comment on the story below.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>范例1：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tAfter drinking from his cup of coffee again, the interior designer slipped his hand in his pants pocket. As he was pulling his hand out, he made sure a pen fell out along with his hand. The item dropped on to the floor. This gave him the reason to get up from his chair, stretch a bit, and bend down to retrieve the fallen item. At this lower vantage point, the interior designer visually checked the underside of the table, and as he imagined before, the listening device was no longer there.</p>\n<p>\n\t想要得到专业主持人的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://st.hujiang.com/topic/169910141921/\" target=\"_blank\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p869682/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p869682\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p756246/\">新概念英语的正确打开方式</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p924449/\">5条建议让你拥有高效的早晨</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p924472/\">2016最值得学的8门口语课程</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"ht